Stuffed Samosa Curry Buns:- You start with making the masala using potato, veggies and curry filling.
Then you stuff the potato curry stuffing in the dough and make round balls.
Then you place the stuffed Samosa curry buns in a baking tray or skillet.
Brush them with whisked egg or a mix of butter.
Bake for 10 minutes till you get a golden crust on top.
Turn off and slather some more butter on each stuffed curry buns.
Serve hot. Would you like to see more?
